Obama's China Blind Date
There are signs of romance blossoming across the Pacific. Why else would President Barack Obama pick Feb. 14, Valentine's Day, to meet with China's president-in-waiting, Xi Jinping?
It's tough to overstate the importance of the meeting between the leader of the world's biggest economy and the soon-to-be leader of its second biggest. Better trade relations could help get the fragile world economy back on its feet; more friction could knock what little wind there is out of the recovery.